## Context

Nineteenth run. Five journal entries, four tasks. Major themes: ontunisertib first anti-fibrotic FSCD trial, bile acid-microbiome infliximab mechanism, biologic-resistant epithelial inflammation, GALAXI-2/3 Phase 3 + duvakitug TL1A maintenance data.

### Journal entries created
- #2530: Ontunisertib (AGMB-129) STENOVA Phase 2a topline — first anti-fibrotic drug in FSCD (n=103, ALK5/TGFβR1 inhibitor, GI-restricted). Primary endpoint met (safety). Positive SES-CD/MRE trends. Phase 2b planned H2 2026. FDA Fast Track.
- #2531: Bile acid-microbiome gatekeeps infliximab efficacy (n=100 CD prospective). Bifidobacterium catenulatum→TCDCA→Treg/M1 mechanism. Microbiome LDA AUC 0.805. Non-responders depleted in Bifidobacterium/Blautia/Lachnospiraceae with TCDCA deficiency.
- #2533: Follicle-associated enterocytes (FAE) drive M1 macrophage cascade UNRESOLVED by biologics in CD ileum (bioRxiv 2025.03.26.645552, 380K cells, 46 donors). Colon: colonocyte→FAP+ stroma→innate immune. Spatial validation. Direct evidence for epithelial reserve hypothesis.
- #2535: GALAXI-2/3 Phase 3 guselkumab (PMID 40684778, Lancet): 36-39% endoscopic response at wk48 vs 5-6% placebo. Duvakitug Phase 2b maintenance (Sanofi Feb 2026): 47.8% induction, 55% (900mg) maintenance endoscopic response in CD. Phase 3 underway. Still no GALAXI biopsy transcriptomics.
- #2536: Multi-omics integration review (Chen UEG J 2025) confirms single-omics insufficient. Bile acid axis (TCDCA) links microbiome to treatment response — relevant for metabolite subtype annotation.

### Tasks created
- #1540 (research_director, P3): Evaluate ontunisertib ALK5/TGFβR1 pathway as benchmark for fibrosis drug screen
- #1541 (research_director, P3): Evaluate Bifidobacterium/bile acid axis as complementary anti-TNF response biomarker
- #1542 (research_director, P2): Integrate FAE→M1 biologic-resistant cascade into epithelial reserve model
- #1543 (research_director, P4): Check TCDCA/bile acid pathway representation in microbiome-metabolome subtypes

### Key highlights for next run
- Ontunisertib Phase 2b (FSCD) planned H2 2026. OLE 48-week results also expected H2 2026. First clinically validated anti-fibrotic mechanism in CD — ALK5 pathway is now the benchmark.
- Duvakitug Phase 2b CD maintenance: 55% endoscopic response at wk44 (900mg) is the strongest TL1A data in CD to date. Phase 3 recruiting. Tulisokibart Phase 3 (ARES-CD) also recruiting. MSD expanding tulisokibart to 3 additional autoimmune indications.
- FAE→M1 cascade (bioRxiv) provides cell-type-specific signatures of biologic-resistant inflammation. Region-specific: ileum (FAE-mediated) vs colon (colonocyte/FAP+ stroma). This is the strongest evidence yet for epithelial-driven treatment resistance.
- Bile acid-microbiome axis: Bifidobacterium/TCDCA now mechanistically linked to infliximab response. Multi-modal classifiers (transcriptomic + microbiome) likely outperform single-omics. Cross-project relevance for anti-TNF and microbiome-metabolome subtyping.
- PALI-2108 FSCD Phase 1b: first patients dosed Oct 2025, topline data was expected Q1 2026 — still no public release. Check again next run.
- DDW 2026: May 2-5 Chicago. Abstracts should be publicly searchable by late April. Mine after conference.
- GALAXI biopsy transcriptomics: still not released despite Phase 3 publication. Monitor for substudy publications.
- Prior monitoring items still pending: SPARC IBD metabolomics (#1065), ARES-CD CDx genotype panel, STENOVA OLE (H2 2026), anti-TNF serum proteomics/HLA-DQB1*03:01 biomarkers, Verstockt GPX4 data deposition check (#1265), Kong/Washburn GEO data deposition.
- Ferroptosis convergence unchanged since last run (5 compartments + ACSL4). No new ferroptosis papers found this cycle.
- Dual-targeted therapy: VICTRIVA (upadacitinib+vedolizumab) still recruiting.
- Next: DDW 2026 abstract mining (after May 2-5), PALI-2108 FSCD topline data, GALAXI biopsy substudies, ontunisertib Phase 2b initiation, duvakitug Phase 3 enrollment updates, FAE preprint peer-reviewed publication.
